In the second episode of Horizons of Leadership, we talk with Professor Peter Schmidt who is senior lecturer at RIT Croatia, where he teaches subjects related to accounting, taxation, inflation, money, and Bitcoin. He is also the mentor of our student Bitcoin Club and a frequent speaker at conferences focused on Bitcoin and the future of finance. Among students, he’s known as: “the professor saving Gen Z from the fiat disaster”. 

In the episode Professor Schmidt walks us through the history of money, the core principles that give it value, and the risks built into today’s monetary system. He explains how inflation and government debt affect everyday people, and why Bitcoin presents a fundamentally different model. The episode also touches on how companies are already adopting Bitcoin, and how education must evolve to prepare students for this shift.

